condition.narrative: ESCP: Prior to the start of project activities and throughout the project implementation, the Recipient shall develop and implementthe terms applicable to the project grievance mechanism.
ESCP: The SEA/SH Action Plan shall be prepared, approved, and disclosed nine months after effectiveness.

Schedule 2. Section I. A.1. (d) Not later than four (4) months after the Effective Date or any later date agreed upon in writingwith the Association, the Recipient shall: (i) set up an accounting and reporting system for the Project with terms of referenceand specifications acceptable to the Association; and (ii) recruit or assign to the Project, (A) an internal auditor, and (B) anaccountant; both in a manner and with terms of reference, experience and qualifications satisfactory to the Association.

Schedule 2. Section I. A.1. (e) Not later than six (6) months after the Effective Date or any later date agreed upon in writingwith the Association, the Recipient shall recruit or assign to the project an external auditor, in a manner and with terms ofreference, experience and qualifications satisfactory to the Association

Schedule 2. Section I. A.2. The Recipient, not later than one (1) month after the Effective Date or any later date agreed upon inwriting with the Association, shall establish and maintain at all times during Project implementation, under the Ministry ofEmployment, Youth, and Sports, a Project Steering Committee (“PSC”), with terms of reference, composition and resourcessatisfactory to the Association, including inter alia representation from the general directorate of the Ministry of EconomicAffairs and Promotion of Productive Sectors, and co-chairmanship to the Ministry of Economic Affairs and Promotion of ProductiveSectors
